13 WHEREAS, he was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
14 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example he made of his life, he
15 made this world a better place in which to live; and
16 WHEREAS, a man of deep and abiding faith, Marvin Gary Simmons was an active member
17 of Pleasant Valley South Baptist Church; and
18 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous man, Marvin Gary Simmons will long be
19 remembered for his love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who
20 had the great fortune of knowing him.
21 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
22 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Marvin Gary Simmons and
23 express their deepest and most sincere regret at his passing.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
25 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
26 family of Marvin Gary Simmons.
